      "content": "In the event of a dispute, the escrow agent's role is to act as a neutral third-party facilitator, rather than a decision-maker. The agent typically follows the terms of the original sale contract and the applicable laws, such as the Ontario Real Estate Association's (OREA) Escrow Guidelines. If a dispute arises, the agent will investigate the claim and work with the parties to resolve the issue through mediation or other means. If necessary, the agent may also involve a third-party mediator or a regulatory body, such as the Ontario Financial Services Commission (OFSC), to help resolve the dispute.",
